INSERT INTO `idc_collections_collection` VALUES (1,'Standardized representation of the TCIA LIDC-IDRI annotations using DICOM','','','DICOM-LIDC-IDRI-Nodules','<p> This dataset contains standardized DICOM representation of the volumetric nodule annotations and characterizations collected by the LIDC/IDRI initiative.</p> \n<p>  Please see the <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"\" url=\"https://doi.org/10.7937/TCIA.2018.h7umfurq\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\"#external-web-warning\">DICOM-LIDC-IDRI-Nodules <i class=\"fa-solid fa-external-link external-link-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i></a> wiki page to learn more about the images and to obtain any supporting metadata for this collection.</p>','2024-03-08',NULL,'Public',875,'','Lung','10.7937/TCIA.2018.h7umfurq','','Tumor segmentations, image features, Software/Source Code','','Chest',1,0,'A','lidc_idri',1,NULL,'ab83115d-efcd-446e-b76c-b6682998b34e','https://doi.org/10.7937/tcia.2018.h7umfurq'),(2,'QIN multi-site collection of Lung CT data with Nodule Segmentations','','','QIN-LungCT-Seg','<p> This collection contains lung nodule segmentations obtained using segmentation tools that participated in the QIN challenge moist run initiative.</p> \n<p>  Please see the <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"\" url=\"https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2015.1BUVFJR7\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\"#external-web-warning\">QIN-LungCT-Seg <i class=\"fa-solid fa-external-link external-link-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i></a> wiki page to learn more about the images and to obtain any supporting metadata for this collection.</p>','2024-03-08',NULL,'Public',31,'','Lung','10.7937/k9/tcia.2015.1buvfjr7','','Tumor segmentations','','Chest',1,0,'A','lidc_idri,lung_phantom,qin_lung_ct,rider_lung_ct',1,NULL,'58c5c36b-6a64-4034-9128-cb981a9c7f2b','https://doi.org/10.7937/k9/tcia.2015.1buvfjr7'),(3,'DICOM SR of clinical data and measurement for breast cancer collections to TCIA','','','DICOM-SR-Breast-Clinical','<p> This collection contains clinical metadata corresponding to several breast imaging collections harmonized into DICOM SR representation, generated by the Data Integration & Imaging Informatics (DI-Cubed) project.</p> \n<p>  Please see the <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"\" url=\"https://doi.org/10.7937/TCIA.2019.wgllssg1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\"#external-web-warning\">DICOM-SR-Breast-Clinical <i class=\"fa-solid fa-external-link external-link-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i></a> wiki page to learn more about the images and to obtain any supporting metadata for this collection.</p>','2024-03-08',NULL,'Public',474,'','Breast Cancer','10.7937/TCIA.2019.wgllssg1','','DICOM SR descriptions of patient characteristics, histopathology, receptor status and clinical findings including measurements.','','Breast',1,0,'A','breast_diagnosis,breast_mri_nact_pilot,ispy1,tcga_brca',1,NULL,'fec41175-9a45-456f-b789-0f60958b9482','https://doi.org/10.7937/tcia.2019.wgllssg1'),(4,'TCGA-PRAD','TCGA-PRAD','TCGA-PRAD','tcga_prad','<p>The <a href=\"http://imaging.cancer.gov/\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Cancer Imaging Program (CIP)</u></a> is working directly with primary investigators from institutes participating in TCGA to obtain and load images relating to the genomic, clinical, and pathological data being stored within the <a href=\"http://tcga-data.nci.nih.gov/\" target=\"_blank\">TCGA Data Portal</a>.&nbsp;Currently this image collection of prostate adenocarcinoma (PRAD) patients can be matched by each unique case identifier with the extensive gene and expression data of the same case from The Cancer Genome Atlas Data Portal to research the link between clinical phenome and tissue genome.<br /><br /></p>\n <p>Please see the <a href=\"\" url=\"https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.YXOGLM4Y\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\"#external-web-warning\" class=\"external-link\">TCGA-PRAD <i class=\"fa-solid fa-external-link external-link-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i></a> page to learn more about the images and to obtain any supporting metadata for this collection.</p>\n','2024-03-08',NULL,'Public',500,'CT, MR, PT, SM','Prostate Cancer','10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.YXOGLM4Y','Clinical, Genomics','','Human','Prostate',1,0,'O','',1,1,'e1cb37dc-87d9-4074-9925-788be68a9ffa','https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.YXOGLM4Y'),(5,'TCGA-BLCA','TCGA-BLCA','TCGA-BLCA','tcga_blca','<p>\n	The Cancer Genome Atlas-Bladder Endothelial Carcinoma (TCGA-BLCA) data collection is part of a larger effort to enhance the TCGA http://cancergenome.nih.gov/ data set with characterized radiological images. The Cancer Imaging Program (CIP), with the cooperation of several of the TCGA tissue-contributing institutions, has archived a large portion of the radiological images of the genetically-analyzed BLCA cases.</p>\n<p>\n	Please see the <a href=\"\" url=\"https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.8LNG8XDR\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\"#external-web-warning\" class=\"external-link\">TCGA-BLCA <i class=\"fa-solid fa-external-link external-link-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i></a> page to learn more about the images and to obtain any supporting metadata for this collection.</p>\n','2024-03-08',NULL,'Public',412,'CR, CT, DX, MR, PT, SM','Bladder Endothelial Carcinoma','10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.8LNG8XDR','Clinical, Genomics','','Human','Bladder',1,0,'O','',1,1,'6157f2cb-aaf8-4f42-9a2c-ce1261863785','https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.8LNG8XDR'),(6,'TCGA-UCEC','TCGA-UCEC','TCGA-UCEC','tcga_ucec','<p>\n	The Cancer Genome Atlas-Uterine Corpus Endometrial Carcinoma (TCGA-UCEC) data collection is part of a larger effort to enhance the TCGA http://cancergenome.nih.gov/ data set with characterized radiological images. The Cancer Imaging Program (CIP) with the cooperation of several of the TCGA tissue-contributing institutions are working to archive a large portion of the radiological images of the genetically-analyzed UCEC cases.</p><br />\n<p>\n	Please see the <a href=\"\" url=\"https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.GKJ0ZWAC\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\"#external-web-warning\" class=\"external-link\">TCGA-UCEC <i class=\"fa-solid fa-external-link external-link-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i></a> page to learn more about the images and to obtain any supporting metadata for this collection.</p>\n','2024-03-08',NULL,'Public',560,'CR, CT, MR, PT, SM','Uterine Corpus Endometrial Carcinoma','10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.GKJ0ZWAC','Clinical, Genomics','','Human','Uterus',1,0,'O','',1,1,'a92cd421-c314-4bdf-8315-94a092065239','https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.GKJ0ZWAC'),(7,'TCGA-HNSC','TCGA-HNSC','TCGA-HNSC','tcga_hnsc','\n<p>The <a href=\"http://imaging.cancer.gov/\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Cancer Imaging Program (CIP)</u></a> is working directly with primary investigators from institutes participating in TCGA to obtain and load images relating to the genomic, clinical, and pathological data being stored within the <a href=\"http://tcga-data.nci.nih.gov/\" target=\"_blank\">TCGA Data Portal</a>. Currently this large PET/CT multi-sequence image collection of  head and neck squamous cell carcinoma (HNSC) patients can be matched by each unique case identifier with the extensive gene and expression data of the same case from The Cancer Genome Atlas Data Portal to research the link between clinical phenome and tissue genome.</p>\n</br>\n<p>Please see the <a href=\"\" url=\"https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.LXKQ47MS\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\"#external-web-warning\" class=\"external-link\">TCGA-HNSC <i class=\"fa-solid fa-external-link external-link-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i></a> page to learn more about the images and to obtain any supporting metadata for this collection.</p>','2024-03-08',NULL,'Public',523,'SM','Head and Neck Squamous Cell Carcinoma','10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.LXKQ47MS','Clinical, Genomics','','Human','Head-Neck',1,0,'O','',1,1,'c5ef1e90-2919-44b9-bee9-93d938792651','https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.LXKQ47MS'),(8,'TCGA-LUSC','TCGA-LUSC','TCGA-LUSC','tcga_lusc','<p>\n	The Cancer Genome Atlas-Lung Squamous Cell Carcinoma (TCGA-LUSC) data collection is part of a larger effort to enhance the TCGA http://cancergenome.nih.gov/ data set with characterized radiological images. The Cancer Imaging Program (CIP) with the cooperation of several of the TCGA tissue-contributing institutions are working to archive a large portion of the radiological images of the LUSC cases.</p>\n<br />\n<p>\n	Please see the <a href=\"\" url=\"https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.TYGKKFMQ\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\"#external-web-warning\" class=\"external-link\">TCGA-LUSC <i class=\"fa-solid fa-external-link external-link-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i></a> page to learn more about the images and to obtain any supporting metadata for this collection.</p>\n','2024-03-08',NULL,'Public',504,'CT, NM, PT, SEG, SM','Lung Squamous Cell Carcinoma','10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.TYGKKFMQ','Clinical, Genomics','','Human','Lung',1,0,'O','',1,1,'a9027ab7-6de6-46b6-99ea-d88341d89fa6','https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.TYGKKFMQ'),(9,'TCGA-KIRP','TCGA-KIRP','TCGA-KIRP','tcga_kirp','\n<p> The <a href=\"http://imaging.cancer.gov/\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Cancer Imaging Program (CIP)</u></a> is working directly with primary investigators from institutes participating in TCGA to obtain and load images relating to the genomic, clinical, and pathological data being stored within the <a href=\"http://tcga-data.nci.nih.gov/\" target=\"_blank\">TCGA Data Portal</a>.&nbsp;Currently this large CT and MR multi-sequence image collection of  kidney renal papillary cell carcinoma (KIRP) patients can be matched by each unique case identifier with the extensive gene and expression data of the same case from The Cancer Genome Atlas Data Portal to research the link between clinical phenome and tissue genome.&nbsp;<br />\n</br><p><a href=\"\" url=\"https://doi.org/10.7937/K9/TCIA.2016.ACWOGBEF\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\"#external-web-warning\" class=\